				<p>Regarding the much awaited Obama speech, anyone unfamiliar with Obama and the occasion would have thought that he was a muslim clergyman describing the past glories of the islamic world, because he was mentioning the holy koran at several points. Luckily, for him, he mentioned he was a christian. Just once! But that was enough for the occasion!</p>
<p>Anyway, he made an eloquent speech, befitting the character and charisma that he exudes. He touched on several issues and presented them clealry, point for point. He couldn&#8217;t elaborate more, perhaps due to the time limitation that he had set.</p>
	
